postlink" href="http://rapidhdd.com/images/740162ClassicStartScreenshot.PNG">http://rapidhdd.com/images/740162Classi ... enshot.PNG</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Ivo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />You can't have it both ways. The search box either has the focus or doesn't. I can't make an exception for the D key. That's just silly.<br /></div><br />That's sad to hear. This is my invisioning of THE perfect start menu, and it sounds like it is either an impossibility, or an improbability. What it it were optional? Would it at least be codeable?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Ivo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />You can disable adding to the recent documents, but I don't think you can do it selectively. That's a Windows thing, not a Classic Shell thing.<br /></div><br />Any idea how to control this through Windows?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=517">Aeed</a> — Sun Mar 31, 2013 2:19 pm</p><hr />
